```cpp
#include <hexi/hexi.h>
#include <vector>
#include <string>
#include <cstdint>

struct NetworkPacket {
    uint32_t packet_id;
    std::string username;
    std::vector<uint32_t> scores;
    std::string metadata;

    void serialise(auto& stream) {
        // Write packet_id as POD type
        stream << packet_id;

        // Write username with prefix using prefixed adaptor
        stream << hexi::prefixed(username);

        // Write scores vector with prefix using prefixed adaptor
        // The operator<< for iterable containers will handle writing the count first
        // followed by the elements (which will be written by write_container)
        stream << hexi::prefixed(scores);

        // Write metadata as null-terminated string using null_terminated adaptor
        stream << hexi::null_terminated(metadata);
    }
};

std::vector<uint8_t> serialize_packet(const NetworkPacket& packet) {
    // Create a buffer to hold the serialized data
    std::vector<uint8_t> buffer;

    // Create a buffer_adaptor for the buffer
    hexi::buffer_adaptor adaptor(buffer);

    // Create a binary_stream using the buffer_adaptor
    hexi::binary_stream stream(adaptor);

    // Call the packet's serialise method with the binary_stream
    packet.serialise(stream);

    // Return the buffer containing the serialized data
    return buffer;
}
```

## Key Implementation Points:

1. **NetworkPacket::serialise method**:
   - Uses `stream << packet_id` for POD type serialization
   - Uses `hexi::prefixed(username)` for length-prefixed string serialization
   - Uses `hexi::prefixed(scores)` for length-prefixed vector serialization (automatically writes count followed by elements via `write_container`)
   - Uses `hexi::null_terminated(metadata)` for null-terminated string serialization

2. **serialize_packet function**:
   - Creates `std::vector<uint8_t>` buffer
   - Creates `hexi::buffer_adaptor` wrapping the buffer
   - Creates `hexi::binary_stream` using the adaptor
   - Calls `packet.serialise(stream)` to perform serialization
   - Returns the populated buffer

This implementation follows the Hexi library conventions as specified in the reference materials, using the appropriate adaptors for each data type and leveraging the library's automatic container serialization capabilities.

